  "prompt": "How can I convert YouTube videos to MP3 on my iPhone?",
  "response": "To convert YouTube videos to MP3 on your iPhone, you can use third-party apps or online services. Here's a step-by-step guide using a popular method:\n\n### Using an Online Converter (Documents by Readdle)\n\n1. **Install the Documents by Readdle app:**\n   - Go to the App Store on your iPhone.\n   - Search for \"Documents by Readdle\" and install it.\n\n2. **Open the YouTube Website:**\n   - Launch the Documents app.\n   - Tap on the browser icon at the bottom of the screen.\n   - Navigate to `youtube.com` and find the video you want to convert.\n\n3. **Copy the YouTube Video URL:**\n   - Once you've selected the video, tap the \"Share\" icon (usually three vertical dots) and select \"Copy link\" to copy the video URL.\n\n4. **Convert the Video to MP3:**\n   - In the same browser within the Documents app, go to a YouTube to MP3 conversion website like `y2mate.com`.\n   - Paste the copied YouTube video URL into the conversion site's input field.\n   - Select the \"MP3\" format for the output.\n   - Tap on the \"Convert\" or \"Start\" button to begin the conversion process.\n\n5. **Download the MP3 File:**\n   - Once the conversion is complete, the website will provide a download link for the MP3 file.\n   - Tap on the download link, and the file will start downloading within the Documents app.\n\n6. **Access Your MP3 File:**\n   - After the download is complete, you can find the MP3 file in the \"Downloads\" section of the Documents app.\n   - You can play the file directly within the app or transfer it to other music apps on your iPhone.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Legal and Copyright Issues:** Make sure you have the right to convert and download the content. Many YouTube videos are protected by copyright, and unauthorized downloading can violate terms of service and copyright laws.\n- **App Store Restrictions:** Apple's App Store has strict policies against apps that directly convert YouTube videos to MP3. That\u2019s why you must use a workaround like the one described above.\n\nIf you're looking for a more straightforward app-based solution, consider using an Android device, as there are more apps available on the Google Play Store that can directly convert YouTube videos to MP3. For iPhone users, the method using Documents by Readdle and an online converter remains one of the most effective workarounds.",
